olive oil
2 potato
1 packet beef mince
1 packet fine breadcrumbs
1 egg
1 cucumber
1 bag salad leaves
½ lemon
1 bag slaw mix
1 packet Grated Parmesan Cheese
1 sachet Berbere seasoning
1 packet Greek-Style Yoghurt

Preheat the oven to 240°C/220°C fan-forced. Cut the potato into wedges, then place on a lined oven tray. Drizzle with olive oil, season with salt and toss to coat. Bake until slightly tender, 20-25 minutes. In the last 5 minutes of cook time, remove the tray from the oven, then sprinkle over the grated Parmesan cheese and bake until golden and crispy.

While the wedges are baking, combine the beef mince, fine breadcrumbs, egg, Berbere seasoning and a good pinch of salt in a large bowl. Using damp hands, roll heaped spoonfuls of the beef mixture into meatballs, then flatten to make 2cm-thick rissoles. Transfer to a plate. You should get 3-4 rissoles per person.

In a large frying, heat a drizzle of olive oil over a medium-high heat. Cook the rissoles in batches until browned and cooked through, 3-4 minutes each side. Transfer to a plate.

TIP: The spice blend will char slightly in the pan, this adds to the flavour!

While the rissoles are cooking, thinly slice the
cucumber. Roughly chop the salad leaves. Zest
the lemon to get a generous pinch, then slice into
wedges. In a small bowl, combine the Greek-style
yoghurt and lemon zest. Season to taste.

In a medium bowl, combine the cucumber, baby spinach, slaw mix, 1/2 the lemon yoghurt, a squeeze of lemon juice and a drizzle of olive oil. Toss to coat and season to taste.

Divide the smokey beef rissoles, Parmesan wedges and cucumber slaw between plates. Serve with the remaining lemon yoghurt and lemon wedges.